# Advanced Django ERP & SaaS Development Rules

## Core Stack
- Backend framework: Django
- API framework: Django REST Framework (DRF)
- Database: PostgreSQL
- Frontend: Bootstrap 5 RTL
- Deployment: Docker + Gunicorn + Nginx
- Authentication: JWT or Session Authentication
- Cache: Redis when needed

---

# Architecture Rules

## Project Structure
- Use scalable app-based architecture.
- Separate each business domain into its own Django app.
- Keep business logic outside views.
- Use:
  - services/
  - selectors/
  - utils/
  - repositories/
  structure when appropriate.

Example:
apps/
users/
inventory/
sales/
purchases/
reports/

## Clean Code
- Write production-ready code only.
- Avoid quick fixes and dirty solutions.
- Use reusable components.
- Avoid duplicated logic.
- Follow SOLID principles.

## Naming
- Use clear English naming conventions.
- Variables and functions must be descriptive.
- Database tables should use meaningful names.

---

# Database Rules

## PostgreSQL
- Optimize queries for large-scale ERP systems.
- Always use indexes for:
  - foreign keys
  - barcode fields
  - search fields
  - frequently filtered columns

## ORM Optimization
- Use:
  - select_related()
  - prefetch_related()
  aggressively where needed.

- Avoid N+1 query problems.

## Migrations
- Create safe migrations.
- Never remove production data automatically.
- Use data migrations carefully.

## Audit Logs
- Track:
  - created_by
  - updated_by
  - timestamps
  - deleted status

## Soft Delete
- Prefer soft delete for ERP systems.
- Never permanently delete critical business data.

---

# ERP Business Logic Rules

## Multi Branch Support
- All systems must support:
  - branches
  - warehouses
  - multiple users
  - centralized management

## Permissions
- Implement role-based permissions.
- Support:
  - admin
  - manager
  - employee
  - data entry
  roles.

## Inventory
- Prevent negative stock unless explicitly allowed.
- Track stock movement history.
- Keep barcode support optimized.

## Financial Safety
- Never modify financial records directly.
- Use transaction-safe database operations.

## Data Integrity
- Use atomic transactions for critical operations.

Example:
with transaction.atomic():

---

# SaaS Rules

## Multi Tenant
- Build scalable SaaS-ready architecture.
- Separate tenant data securely.
- Never expose tenant data across accounts.

## Security
- Validate all permissions server-side.
- Prevent privilege escalation.
- Protect APIs with authentication and throttling.

## Backups
- Systems must be backup-friendly.
- Design with disaster recovery in mind.

---

# API Rules

## DRF Standards
- Use ViewSets where appropriate.
- Use serializers properly.
- Keep APIs RESTful.

## API Responses
- Return clean JSON responses.

Example:
{
  "success": true,
  "message": "Item created successfully",
  "data": {}
}

## Pagination
- Use pagination for large datasets.

## Filtering
- Use:
  - django-filter
  - search filters
  - ordering filters

## Validation
- Never trust frontend data.
- Validate everything in serializers.

---

# Authentication Rules

## JWT
- Prefer JWT authentication for APIs.

## Permissions
- Use custom permissions when needed.
- Protect all sensitive endpoints.

## Sessions
- Expire inactive sessions securely.

---

# Frontend Rules

## UI Framework
- Use Bootstrap 5 only.
- Design must look modern and enterprise-level.

## RTL
- Always support Arabic RTL layout.
- Navbar and tables must fully support RTL.

## Components
- Create reusable UI components.
- Use:
  - cards
  - responsive tables
  - dashboards
  - charts
  professionally.

## UX
- Prioritize:
  - speed
  - simplicity
  - readability

---

# Django Admin Rules

## Admin Optimization
- Add:
  - search
  - filters
  - autocomplete
  - pagination

## Large Data
- Optimize admin for large ERP datasets.

---

# Performance Rules

## Caching
- Use Redis caching where beneficial.

## Query Optimization
- Avoid unnecessary database hits.

## Static Files
- Optimize static file delivery.

## Async Tasks
- Use Celery for:
  - reports
  - emails
  - heavy background jobs

---

# Security Rules

## Prevent Vulnerabilities
- Protect against:
  - SQL Injection
  - XSS
  - CSRF
  - IDOR
  - Mass Assignment

## Secrets
- Never hardcode secrets.
- Use environment variables.

## Uploads
- Validate uploaded files securely.

---

# Docker Rules

## Containers
- Use separate containers for:
  - web
  - database
  - redis
  - celery

## Environment
- Use .env files.

## Production
- Use Gunicorn + Nginx.

---

# Coding Standards

## Python
- Follow PEP8.
- Use type hints where possible.

## Readability
- Functions should remain short and clean.

## Comments
- Add comments only for complex logic.

---

# Reporting Rules

## Reports
- ERP systems must support:
  - Excel export
  - PDF export
  - filtering
  - date ranges

## Data Tables
- Use server-side pagination for large tables.

